The paper discusses the privacy properties of biometric system architectures and how to reason about them in a formal way. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of formal methods, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of smart cards, which could place it in the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB) as smart cards are often used for secure storage and retrieval of data. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of design choices on privacy guarantees, which could place it in the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it relates to the user experience and interface design.
